td.p:
This request for a preliminary ruling concerns the interpretation of the Agreement establishing an Association between the European Economic Community and Turkey signed on 12 September 1963 at Ankara by the Republic of Turkey, of the one part, and the Member States of the EEC and the Community, of the other part, and concluded, approved and confirmed on behalf of the Community by Council Decision 64/732/EEC of 23 December 1963 (
OJ 1973 C 113, p. 1
) (‘the EEC-Turkey Agreement’); the Additional Protocol signed on 23 November 1970 at Brussels, annexed to the EEC-Turkey Agreement, and concluded, approved and confirmed on behalf of the Community by Council Regulation (EEC) No 2760/72 of 19 December 1972 (
OJ 1973 C 113, p. 17
) (‘the Additional Protocol’); and Decision No 1/95 of the EC-Turkey Association Council of 22 December 1995 on implementing the final phase of the Customs Union (
OJ 1996 L 35, p. 1
) (‘Decision No 1/95 of the Association Council’).

1.   Community licence in accordance with Regulation (EC) No 1072/2009 [of the European Parliament and of the Council of 21 October 2009 on common rules for access to the international road haulage market (
OJ 2009 L 300, p. 72
)];
